                            <comment id="17526857" author="adelapena" created="Sat, 23 Apr 2022 13:16:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The problem happens when &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/blob/b3842de5cf1fa1b81872effb4585fbc7e1873d59/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/config/GuardrailsOptions.java#L696-L714&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;&lt;tt&gt;GuardrailsOptions.validateDataDiskUsageMaxDiskSize&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/a&gt; validates the new &lt;tt&gt;data_disk_usage_max_disk_size&lt;/tt&gt; property to see if there is enough physical size.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I have moved the calculation of the physical disk space to a separate method on &lt;tt&gt;DiskUsageMonitor&lt;/tt&gt; and added a Byteman rule to the test intercepting calls to that method. That way the test should always operate with a fixed disk size, independently of the testing machine.&lt;/p&gt;
